There are a couple special situations. For all the weapon skills (including unarmed) when calculating averages only use the highest weapon skill in the calculation. Instead of having separate rows for each weapon we just a single Weapon Skill row. For example if a character has a 8 in Axes and a 0 is Short Blades at level 10, and another charcter has 0 in Axes and 8 in Short Blades, the modified average will be 8 for the Weapon Skill at level 10.

We will use a similar algorithm for Spell Schools, but calculate the Top 3 for each. For example:

Game 1:

Conjuration: 0
Alchemy: 8
Fire Elem.: 6
Necromancy: 6

Game 2:
Conjuration: 6
Alchemy: 8
Fire Elem.: 0
Necromancy: 6

Modified Average:

Conjuration: 6
Alchemy: 8
Fire Elem.: 6
Necromancy: 6

So we don't count spell school values into the average that are outside the top 3 for a particular game. 